data.shownotes: This show featured the debut of Ice V. Wah Wah began with the intro to The River, and subsequently contained Crumbling Castle and The River teases. Ambrose quoted It Ain't Me, Babe (Bob Dylan) before Doom City. O.N.E. began with the intro to Straws in the Wind instead of the customary intro. Pleura contained a quote of “Freedom” (Rage Against the Machine). Straws in the Wind was dedicated to Russell Brand. Smoke and Mirrors was played over the PA as the setbreak music. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo. Ambergris contained an Ice V tease. Before The Reticent Raconteur, Leah Senior was introduced to the stage as “The Original Balrog” and Joey gave a shoutout to her live bass player Jack [Robbins], with the bonus trivia that he was also in Stu’s first band Almacknjack. The Reticent Raconteur was played for the first time since 2021-02-24 (61 show gap). The Reticent Raconteur and The Lord of Lightning featured narration by Leah Senior. The Fourth Colour was played for the first time since 2019-11-23 (70 show gap). Am I in Heaven? contained The Dripping Tap teases. Poster by Jason Galea 800 standard / 50 Foil Print

This show featured the live debut of Magma. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo. The Garden Goblin was introduced by Cookie as a song that he wrote about his dog. Leah Senior was shouted out after Magma. Rattlesnake contained Doom City, O.N.E., Honey, Nuclear Fusion, Billabong Valley, & Automation teases and quotes and Sleep Drifter teases.

Poster Art by Jason Galea
130 Standard / 30 Foil Print

This show featured the live debut of A New World. Slow Jam 1 contained Ice V and Flamethrower teases, as well as Iron Lung quotes. The Grim Reaper featured an additional verse from Sadie Sorceress played over the music to The Grim Reaper followed by Sadie Sorceress quotes and teases. Ice V contained Slow Jam 1 quotes. A New World through Altered Beast II featured narration by Leah Senior. Altered Beast I was played for the first time since 2022-10-05 (90 show gap). Alter Me I and Altered Beast II were played for the first time since 2019-10-06 (87 show gap). Work This Time featured a guitar solo. Leah Senior was shouted out after Magma. The Dripping Tap contained Hypertension quotes and Hell’s Itch and Head On/Pill teases.

Poster by Jason Galea
320 Standard / 40 Foil Print

Sleep Drifter contained Honey quotes and teases and O.N.E., Billabong Valley, and Rattlesnake teases. Ambrose quoted “Fuck tha Police” (N.W.A) in Billabong Valley. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo. Leah Senior was shouted out before Magma. Poster by Jason Galea 220 Standard / 30 Foil
This was an in-studio appearance for radio station KEXP in Seattle. Following Magma the band had a 10 minute interview with KEXP DJ/on-air events coordinator Cheryl Waters.

An I In Heaven? was teased prior to Magenta Mountain. The intro to O.N.E. contained Straws in the Wind teases. The River contained Wah Wah teases and quotes throughout, as well as Crumbling Castle teases. The Land Before Timeland was played over the PA as the setbreak music, which incidentally served as the “debut” for the studio track. Rattlesnake contained teases and quotes from O.N.E., Automation, Honey, and Minimum Brain Size, and teases of Sleep Drifter. Honey contained teases of Sleep Drifter and Billabong Valley. The Reticent Raconteur through The Balrog featured Leah Senior (introduced as “The Balrog” and “the best singer”) providing the narration. Ambrose quoted “Happy Birthday, Lisa” (The Simpsons) while referencing Joey’s “Australian birthday” prior to The Grim Reaper. The Grim Reaper was then introduced as “some weird-ass Satanic rap”. Venusian 2 and Am I in Heaven? were on the printed setlist but were replaced with Planet B due to time constraints. This show was released through the Official Bootlegger program as part of Live at Red Rocks ‘22. Poster By Jason Galea This is the first edition of this print
Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo over a metal vamp from the band. Ambrose quoted “Evergreen” (Leah Senior) before The Dripping Tap. Poster By Jason Galea 230 Standard / 30 Foil

The show opened with a brief drum solo by Cavs prior to the rest of the band taking the stage. History owner (Drake) (“Champagne Papi”) was mentioned a number of times over the course of the show. Rattlesnake contained O.N.E. and Automation quotes and teases. Ambrose crowd surfed while singing the refrain in Straws in the Wind. Joey introduced Anoxia as “my Neil Young impersonation song.” Ice V was introduced as being “in memory of Queen E.” Prior to Digital Black, Joey said "hello" numerous times in a Han-Tyumi impression. Soy-Protein Munt Machine and Vomit Coffin contained Hypertension teases. The Dripping Tap contained an I’m in Your Mind Fuzz Suite tease. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The recordings of this show are incomplete (missing Digital Black). KGLW.net staff do have enough to confirm the > into Han-Tyumi and that Ice V came to a full stop. For the show opening drum solo, it was discussed whether this should be added to the setlist as “Fury” in order to match with the show opening drum solo from the Melbourne ‘21 bootlegger release. It was decided that the drum solos labeled “Fury” by the band consist of a distinct double bass drum part which is absent from this drum solo and that other drum solos have been given different names (i.e. “Parking” on Chunky Shrapnel), therefore it was decided to leave this drum solo as a show note since we do not have definitive information on what it should be called. If anyone has any further information about these items, or ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net. Poster By Carlo Vivary

Her and I contained Hell's Itch teases.  After The Fourth Colour, Joey asks the crowd to “take a step back”. The Grim Reaper contained Sadie Sorceress quotes. Alter Me III and Altered Beast IV were performed with Leah Senior providing the narration. Alter Me III and Altered Beast IV were played for the first time since 2019-10-08 (96 show gap). Evil Death Roll contained Alter Me teases, Hell's Itch teases and a Hypertension Jam, which would debut properly the following night.

Poster By Arash Zarifian
Standard 250 / 30 Foil Prints

It was announced prior to the show that Stu was late to the stage because he had “diarrhea or something”. Stu then entered the stage costumed as “Disco Stu” and noted that it was his birthday show. After Hell, Stu teased "Stayin' Alive" (Bee Gees). Persistence was stopped partway through for a cake “being fucked by a sexy alien” to be presented to Stu, and for the crowd and band to sing “Happy Birthday to You” to Stu, after which Stu passed out the cake to the audience and several jokes were made about the cake's contents. Persistence was finished after the mid-song break. The River contained Wah Wah teases and an Ice V tease. Leah Senior was shouted out before Lava. At the end of the show, Stu was hit with silly string by the band while the audience sang to him again. KGLW.net Staff Notes: Fans of stage banter will want to listen to this show for humorous birthday comments throughout the show, and other amusing banter about being drunk and the Satanic nuns that often appear at their shows. Poster By Josh Freydkis

Rattlesnake contained Sleep Drifter teases. The outro to Sleep Drifter contained Honey quotes before returning to the earlier Rattlesnake jam. Before Pleura, the band shouted out The Murlocs (with Cavs filling in on drums) for killing it prior to their set. Before Gaia, it was noted that Fishing for Fishies had been recorded by Gareth Liddiard of Tropical Fuck Storm. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo over a metal vamp from the band. Before The Dripping Tap, Joey again shouted out The Murlocs, Leah Senior, and “Tropical Fuck Cunts”. KGLW.net Staff Notes: For those wondering about the nature of the show-opening Rattlesnake sequence, the band is jamming on Rattlesnake themes before an immediate and natural transition to Honey, which is immediately followed by a segue into Sleep Drifter that contains elements of Honey all the way through, and finally a return to the bridge and “Rattle, rattle, rattle” portion of the preceding Rattlesnake jam, thus completing the “Snake Sandwich”.

“Theme from Halloween” was played over the PA prior to the costumed band members walking on stage to a song played over the PA: "P.I.M.P" (50 Cent) for Ambrose, dressed as a pimp, "Mother" (Danzig) for Cavs, dressed as Glenn Danzig, "You've Got a Friend in Me" (Randy Newman) for Lucas, dressed as Buzz Lightyear, ""C" is for Cookie" (Sesame Street) for Cook, dressed as a cookie, with him throwing cookies into the crowd, "Oompa Loompa (#1)" (Willy Wonka & the Chocolate Factory) for Joey, dressed as an Oompa Loompa, and "Hollaback Girl" (Gwen Stefani) for Stu, dressed as a banana and throwing bananas into the crowd. Additionally, crew for the show were dressed as ketchup and mustard bottles. Robot Stop contained a Hot Water tease. Alter Me was teased during the intro to People-Vultures. Mr. Beat contained a Persistence tease. Before Alter Me II, there was an extended discussion about bananas. Alter Me II through Altered Beast IV were performed with Leah Senior (dressed as a witch) providing the narration. The verses were sung out of order in Altered Beast IV. Let Me Mend The Past contained an It Ain't Me, Babe (Bob Dylan) quote. Before Doom City, Stu denied a fan request for Catching Smoke saying that they didn’t know how to play it. Magenta Mountain featured a lyric change to reference Willy Wonka and the Chocolate Factory. Stu removed the banana costume prior to Self-Immolate and threw it into the crowd, citing that it was “too hot”. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo over a metal vamp from the band in which Ambrose destroyed pumpkins that were on stage and threw the pieces into the crows. Poster by Jake Foreman

The band introduced the show by acknowledging how little they play hometown shows, citing Melbourne inner-city gentrification. Crumbling Castle was then introduced as “The Fourth Colour”, “Crumbling Castle”, and finally, “Gamma Knife”. The Fourth Colour featured a Cavs drum solo. The Grim Reaper was introduced as a song that Ambrose wrote about Stu, and featured an additional verse and quotes from Sadie Sorceress. Stu sang the third verse twice instead of the second verse in Ice V. Iron Lung was introduced as a “song about vaping”. Ambergris was introduced as a song about “the most expensive naturally occurring ingredient”. Float Along - Fill Your Lungs contained a Dragon jam.

This show was part of the 2022 Summer Haze Festival. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo over the top of a metal vamp from the band. Ice V contained Hypertension teases. Stu threw water bottles into the crowd during Hot Water. Amusing banter before The Dripping Tap referenced the heat, sweating, church, God, Satan, weed, and vaping. The Dripping Tap subsequently contained Hypertension teases and quotes. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The recording for this show is incomplete (missing Hypertension). Despite the incomplete recording, KGLW.net staff supports the -> transition from Ice V -> Hypertension based on available audio evidence of the start of the transition near the end of Ice V. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

This show was originally scheduled to be at Bowl of Brooklands, but was moved indoors to TSB Stadium due to weather. I’m Not in Your Mind contained The Dripping Tap teases and Alter Me teases and quotes. The River contained Happy Birthday to You quotes and eventually came to a full stop as Sam’s birthday was recognized by the band and crowd. Ice V subsequently contained The River teases. Work This Time featured a guitar solo. The Dripping Tap contained teases from the I’m In Your Mind Fuzz Suite before reprising Cellophane.
People-Vultures contained a “Down With the Sickness” (Disturbed) quote. Mr. Beat contained The Dripping Tap teases. Automation was dedicated to ChatGPT. Poster By Carlo Vivary

Sleep Drifter contained Rattlesnake and O.N.E. teases. The Book was introduced as a song about Satan and featured a Cavs drum solo. Evil Death Roll contained a Robot Stop tease. Lava contained Hypertension and Superposition teases. Slow Jam 1 contained Ice V teases, Iron Lung quotes and Witchcraft teases. Self-Immolate featured another Cavs drum solo. Gila Monster was introduced as “a song about dragons and witches and shit”.

Poster By Carlo Vivary

Let Me Mend The Past contained an It Ain't Me, Babe (Bob Dylan) quote. Sense was teased immediately before and during Ice V, which contained a Hypertension tease. Ambergris was introduced as “Joey’s porno song”. The Dripping Tap contained Hot Water teases and quotes with the lyrics changed to “time to party” and “everybody wants to party”, and Cellophane teases. Boogieman Sam contained “Going Up the Country” (Canned Heat), “Got My Mojo Working” (Ann Cole), “My Babe” (Little Walter) and “It's a Long Way to the Top (If You Wanna Rock 'N' Roll)” (AC/DC) quotes and Am I In Heaven? teases. Float Along – Fill Your Lungs contained a metal jam. Poster By Lewy Jones

Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs. Gila Monster was introduced as a track off a new album, after which Stu shouted out drop D tuning. Let Me Mend The Past contained an It Ain't Me, Babe (Bob Dylan) quote. Ice V contained quotes of "Ain’t It Funky Now" and “The Boss” (James Brown). The intro to Gamma Knife contained People-Vultures and Robot Stop teases. Amby quoted “So Long, Farewell” (The Sound of Music) after Iron Lung. Poster By Carlo Vivary

Evil Death Roll was introduced as a song about crocodiles and contained The Dripping Tap and Trapdoor teases.  Alter Me I contained Ice V teases.  Billabong Valley and Honey contained Sleep Drifter teases.  Ambrose quoted Polygondwanaland before Inner Cell. The Grim Reaper contained Torture Chamber quotes and an extra verse from Sadie Sorceress.  Los Bitchos joined the band for Trapdoor, which contained a percussion solo.

Poster by Lewy Jones

The Grim Reaper contained an extra verse from Sadie Sorceress. Shanghai was stopped midway through, eventually resuming with a Grow Wings and Fly 'Lets Get Real High' jam. The Bitter Boogie contained Crumbling Castle teases. Prior to Lava, a pocket watch was passed up to the stage and Stu attempted to find the owner. Lava contained Hypertension teases. Wah Wah contained The River teases/quotes. It’s Got Old was played for the first time since April 13, 2022 (84 show gap) and was introduced as “a very old song that will most likely be fucking awesome and very reggae-ish” as well as containing a Blindness (The Fall) jam. Ice V had the intro and first verse performed without drums and contained Hypertension teases. Prior to The Dripping Tap, Amby introduced the song as the story of his kitchen sink and Joey shouted out one of the front-of-stage security staff who had been dancing to the music. The Dripping Tap contained Cellophane teases and closed with Amby quoting “So Long, Farewell” (The Sound of Music). Poster By Drew Millward

Stu joined the opener Los Bitchos on flute for their cover of Trapdoor. Rattlesnake contained O.N.E. teases and had some of the "rattle, rattle, rattle" refrains changed to "boogie, boogie, boogie". Automation contained a false intro with Cavs playing the drumbeat to Muddy Water. Honey contained Rattlesnake quotes (with the "rattle, rattle, rattle" refrain changed to "Brussels, Brussels, Brussels"), Sleep Drifter teases and O.N.E. teases. An audience member named Mīkal was brought onstage to do the vocal intro to Nuclear Fusion. The O.N.E. intro contained Straws in the Wind teases. Magenta Mountain was introduced as a song about monkeys, then as a song about Lucas. Planet B was introduced as a song about monkeys, then space monkeys and finally "human monkeys". Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs followed by a brief metal vamp by the band. Planet B and Self-Immolate were dedicated to Michael Badger, a sound engineer/mixer on the studio versions of the tracks. I'm Not In Your Mind contained Witchcraft teases, Am I in Heaven? teases, The Dripping Tap teases/quotes and Hot Water teases/quotes with lyrics changed to "time to party". Cellophane contained "animals in Australia" quotes. The Balrog contained Evil Death Roll teases and Hypertension teases & quotes. Boogieman Sam had some of the "boogie, boogie, boogie" refrains changed to "Brussels, Brussels, Brussels" and contained “Whole Lotta Rosie” (AC/DC) teases, “Got My Mojo Working” (Ann Cole) quotes, “Going Up the Country” (Canned Heat) quotes, “Hells Bells” (AC/DC) teases, "animals in Australia" quotes, and Hypertension teases. Evil Death Roll and Presumptuous were on the printed setlist but were not played. Poster By Mr. Joe Johnson

The Wheel was played for the first time since Dec. 19, 2021 (94 show gap). Alter Me III contained Witchcraft teases. Altered Beast IV contained Converge teases. Sadie Sorceress was dedicated to Ambrose's 99-year-old grandmother and contained an extra verse from The Grim Reaper and quotes of Torture Chamber. Am I In Heaven? contained “animals in Australia” lyrics, Witchcraft teases, Head On/Pill teases, Ice V teases, Hot Water teases, Shanghai teases, The Dripping Tap teases, I Am Not a Man Unless I Have a Woman quotes and Sea of Trees teases. Poster By Jason Galea 100 Standard / 30 Foil

Wah Wah contained The River teases. Ambergris was introduced as a song about whale vomit. Hypertension contained Iron Lung quotes. Iron Lung contained Hypertension teases and Ice V teases. Before Shanghai, which was introduced as a song about how the band almost broke up over a hot pot, but it was alright because they all turned into butterflies afterward, Stu asked the crowd if they had even seen the band at various Sydney venues (Goodgod, World Bar), then Ambrose sung some of Lunch Meat. Shanghai featured a Grow Wings and Fly jam. The Grim Reaper featured an additional verse from Sadie Sorceress. Hell and Predator X were on the written setlist but were not played. Poster By Rowena Lloyd

This show was part of the 2023 Vintage Vibes Festival. Ice V contained Iron Lung quotes. Gaia contained a drum solo from Cavs. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but no recordings are available. KGLW.net staff believes the setlist is complete based on contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

This show featured the debut of Converge.  Iron Lung was introduced as a song about vaping.  Self-Immolate was introduced as a song about setting yourself on fire and featured the return of the Holy Explorer to the stage.  Gaia was dedicated to Russell Crowe.  The show was stopped for several minutes during Gila Monster in order to find a missing person.

data.jamchart_notes: Spanning almost 15 minutes, this high energy rendition takes a brief but exciting detour into a metal-esque jam.
data.shownotes: This show featured the debut of Astroturf. Following the Mind Fuzz suite Amby quoted “Runnin’ With the Devil” (Van Halen). Magenta Mountain had lyrics changed to “I don’t believe Stu, his eyes deceive you.” Magenta Mountain contained a tease of The Grim Reaper. The Grim Reaper contained Torture Chamber quotes and featured an additional verse from Sadie Sorceress. Shanghai was on the printed setlist following The Grim Reaper and was attempted but not played due to technical difficulties. Ice V contained a Blindness (The Fall) jam. Poster By Jason Galea 215 Standard / 80 Foil Print

Scheduled opening band Kamikaze Palm Tree’s set was cancelled due to an inclement weather warning. Rattlesnake contained Sleep Drifter teases/quotes, Honey teases and Boogieman Sam quotes, and had some of the “rattle, rattle, rattle” refrains changed to “boogie, boogie, boogie.”  Slow Jam 1 was introduced as "probably [Ambrose's] favorite song of ours" and contained Iron Lung and Her and I (Slow Jam 2) quotes.  Hell contained a Superbug outro.  Ambergris and The Great Chain of Being were on the printed setlist but were not played.

Poster By Jason Galea
2000 Standard / 500 Foil

Rattlesnake contained Honey teases and Sleep Drifter teases/quotes. Honey contained Rattlesnake teases and Sleep Drifter teases. Shanghai featured a Grow Wings and Fly “let’s get real high” jam. Stu teased “Voodoo Child (Slight Return)” (Jimi Hendrix) during the leadup to Invisible Face. Invisible Face was played for the first time since June 6, 2017 (313 show gap) and was performed in full for the first time. Wah Wah contained The River teases. Ice V contained "Ain’t It Funky Now" (James Brown) teases. Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs, during which Amby burned his copy of the setlist. This show was released through the Official Bootlegger program as part of Live in Chicago '23. KGLW.net Staff Notes: Invisible Face appears in setlists 40 times prior to this show. Of these, 29 have no recording available and one recording cuts off before the end of the song. The remaining 10 are all complete recordings of unfinished versions in which only the first two verses are performed. Based on these facts and the comments made by the band at this show, KGLW.net staff believe that the unavailable versions were also unfinished and that this is the first complete performance of Invisible Face. If anyone has conclusive evidence to the contrary, please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net. Poster By Jason Galea 460 Standard / 130 Foil

Joey shouted-out other performers at the festival: Yeah Yeah Yeahs, Sam Fender, Flume, Little Simz, and Marlon Williams. Joey acknowledged that the performance was taking place on stolen land, that the band will be voting yes in the upcoming Indigenous voice to Parliament referendum, and that the audience should do the same. KGLW.net Staff Notes: Special shout out to our very own @W.B.T.G. Slinger for the recording located on Archive.org and YouTube!
Ice V Contained Am I In Heaven? teases.  Iron Lung contained Hypertension teases.

Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs.  This Thing contained teases & quotes of The Dripping Tap.

Poster By Mathias Krebser
160 Standard Print
Evil Death Roll contained Converge and Chang'e teases. The Grim Reaper contained Torture Chamber quotes and "Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) quotes. Poster By Emy Rojas

Head On/Pill contained Witchcraft teases, Ice V teases and a Motor Spirit jam. Ice V contained Witchcraft teases. Hypertension contained teases of The Dripping Tap, Am I In Heaven? and People-Vultures. The Grim Reaper contained quotes of Torture Chamber, "Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) and “Sabotage” (Beastie Boys). Poster by Bassant Ahmed

data.jamchart_notes: Coming out of Hypertension and landing halfway through a great sequence of segues, the second jam is where the magic happens. Landing on the wrong key, an atypical jam emerges from the breakdown, with the band modulating back and forth between the key the band landed in and the song's original key to great effect. Following the final verse, they break it down with some Her and I and Presumptuous teases, before executing great segue into Presumptuous.
data.shownotes:
Iron Lung contained Hypertension teases.  Hypertension contained Evil Death Roll teases.  Ice V contained Presumptuous and Her and I teases.  Hot Water contained The Dripping Tap quotes and teases.  This Thing contained Hot Water quotes.

Poster By Max Löffler
data.venuename: Plaza Mayor de El Poble Espanyol

data.shownotes: The Grim Reaper featured “I’m the Shrimp Reaper” vocals and contained quotes of Torture Chamber, Sadie Sorceress, "Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) and “One, Two, Freddy’s Coming For You” (A Nightmare on Elm Street) with lyrics changed to “Shrimpy’s coming for you.” Static Electricity was introduced as a song about the time Stu almost got electrocuted in Thailand. O.N.E. contained Straws In The Wind teases. Boogieman Sam contained Rattlesnake quotes, The Bitter Boogie teases and quotes; “La Grange” (ZZ Top) teases and quotes, “Going Up the Country” (Canned Heat) quotes, The Dripping Tap teases, “Whole Lotta Rosie” (AC/DC) teases and “Tutti Frutti” (Little Richard) quotes. The Dripping Tap contained Hell's Itch teases and a Witchcraft jam. Poster By Job van Rijen

The Grim Reaper contained Torture Chamber and "Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) quotes. Evil Death Roll contained Converge teases. Rattlesnake contained Boogieman Sam quotes and Flamethrower teases. K.G.L.W. (Outro) was on the printed setlist after Rattlesnake but was not played. Poster by Drew Millward

This was King Gizzard's first show in South America. Head On/Pill contained Robot Stop teases and Am I In Heaven? teases & quotes.  Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases & quotes.  Venusian 2 contained Converge quotes.

This show featured the first full performance of Motor Spirit. Rattlesnake was introduced as a song about snakes and contained Honey and Doom City teases. Honey contained a Sleep Drifter jam. Open Water featured a drum solo by Cavs. Ice V contained Hog Calling Contest teases. Cut Throat Boogie contained Sad Pilot teases and Rats In The Sky, Raw Feel, Field of Vision and Daily Blues quotes. Most Of What I Like contained a “Praise You” (Fatboy Slim) jam with Flight b741 teases. Following Most Of What I Like, Stu teased “Sweet Home Alabama” (Lynyrd Skynyrd). The Lord of Lightning was introduced as a song about shots by Stu, and about when Stu got struck by lightning by Ambrose, and contained Cut Throat Boogie and I'm In Your Mind teases. The Alter Me I Jam contained a Hypertension jam with lyrics and Witchcraft and Cellophane teases. I'm Not In Your Mind contained Robot Stop teases. Cellophane was also introduced as a song about shots by Stu and contained Motor Spirit quotes. Joey shouted out opener Grace Cummings after I'm In Your Mind Fuzz. Dragon was introduced as a song about dragons. Poster by Amy Jean; Edition of 100

This show featured the debut of Raw Feel. Grace Cummings unfortunately missed a fourth show due to illness, and was replaced with Atlanta, Georgia psych-punk band Upchuck, who Joey thanked at the beginning of the show. Gamma Knife contained an intro jam and Motor Spirit teases. The Dripping Tap, which contained a Head On/Pill tease, had Stu's amp break in the middle, which lead to the song being paused for a short time during which Joey teased “Hey Joe” (Jimi Hendrix) followed by a quote from Ambrose. Nuclear Fusion featured audience member, Earl, on vocals. Honey contained a Sleep Drifter intro that contained Nuclear Fusion teases, and the song itself contained Billabong Valley, Straws In The Wind, and O.N.E teases. Straws In The Wind contained a chant of 'Free Palestine'. Venusian 2 was on the printed setlist after Perihelion but was not played. Poster by Amy Jean; Edition of 150

Gondii contained Extinction quotes and The Grim Reaper quotes and teases. A segue into The Grim Reaper out of Gondii was attempted but scrapped, and led to The Grim Reaper being skipped. Before Evil Death Roll, Stu teased Voodoo Child (Slight Return) and Little Wing (both by Jimi Hendrix). Joey yelled Free Palestine in Pleura. Poster by Amy Jean; Edition of 100

This show featured the debut of Antarctica. The Dripping Tap contained Chang'e teases, You Can Be Your Silhouette teases, Antarctica teases & quotes, and Am I In Heaven? teases. Evil Death Roll was introduced as a song about Bob Dylan and contained Witchcraft and Robot Stop teases. Ice V contained a Witchcraft tease and a "Blindness" (The Fall) jam. The Fourth Colour, which was incomplete, contained a Daily Blues jam with lyrics and "Whole Lotta Rosie" (AC/DC) teases. Supercell was introduced as a song about orange juice. Following Motor Spirit, Joey introduced the band members. Gaia contained a jam with Joey on bass, which contained a Motor Spirit tease and a drum solo.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition of 650
Holographic Edition of 200

Hot Water contained Robot Stop, Am I In Heaven?, and The Dripping Tap teases. Robot Stop, which was incomplete, contained Ice V, Daily Blues, and Am I In Heaven? teases and Field of Vision quotes. The second Hot Water contained a chant of "New York City". Ice V contained a "Blindness" (The Fall) jam and improvised lyrics. The Bitter Boogie contained the drums from Muddy Water and Ice V teases. You Can Be Your Silhouette was introduced as a song about being who you want to be. Hot Wax contained You Can Be Your Silhouette teases. Converge was introduced as a song about storms before Planet B, as Stu confused them on the setlist. The Great Chain of Being contained an "On The Road Again" (Canned Heat) tease. Motor Spirit was dedicated to Cavs "because it's about cars" and contained a You Can Be Your Silhouette and Robot Stop tease. Slow Jam 1 contained Crumbling Castle, Sad Pilot and Ice V teases. Billabong Valley was preceded by a "Microtonal Jazz Jam" with Stu referencing Sexy Alien and Joey singing The Star Spangled Banner. In the song itself, Ambrose crowdsurfed on an inflatable gator and quoted Should I Stay Or Should I Go (The Clash). Following Automation, Joey shouted out opener Geese. A crowd member then told the band to play Fishing For Fishies and the full band (besides Cavs) teased it. The band then started to name classic rock songs and teased Stairway To Heaven and Moby Dick (both Led Zeppelin), and Smoke On the Water (Deep Purple). Stu also shouted out Australian band Cold Chisel. Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg contained a Hypertension tease. Am I In Heaven? contained Evil Death Roll, and Converge teases and Hot Water teases and quotes. Sad Pilot was on the printed setlist but was skipped.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition of 1200
Holographic Edition of 300

Before Magma, Joey thanked Geese for opening. Muddy Water contained the drums from The Bitter Boogie along with teases, and featured Ambrose on sax. Raw Feel contained a Sympathy For the Devil (The Rolling Stones) tease. Ice V featured Jimi Hendrix-style scat vocals from Joey. Joey introduced Le Risque as a song about taking risks. Before Superbug, Joey told Stu not to write another song like it because he wrote it and it (Covid) happened. Superbug was played for the first time since 2023-06-07 (59 show gap). Before Dragon, Killing in the Name (Rage Against the Machine) was teased. Dragon was not on the printed setlist but was played.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition - 500
Foil Edition - 150

Hypertension contained Boogieman Sam teases and quotes and Ice V teases. Ice V contained Hypertension and Blindness (The Fall) teases. Antarctica contained an outro jam without drums for Cavs to take a piss break. Before Gaia, Stu joked about how Supercell sounds like "soup for sale". Gaia contained a drum solo during which fans gave shirts to Stu. Before Mars For the Rich Stu put a hat (that he had earlier picked up from the stage) on backwards, jokingly compared himself to Lleyton Hewitt (an Australian former tennis player who was known for wearing hats backwards), and imitated his trademark fist pump. Swan Song (#2) contained Dragon quotes. Float Along - Fill Your Lungs contained a Dragon jam with lyrics.

Rattlesnake contained Automation and Sleep Drifter teases, Boogieman Sam quotes and Nuclear Fusion teases. O.N.E. and Sleep Drifter featured Stu on microtonal acoustic guitar. Open Water contained a Chang’e tease. The Lord of Lightning contained an Ice V tease. The Balrog contained a Cellophane tease. Before Hog Calling Contest, Joey mentioned that the band saw Dom Dolla at The Gorge the night before. Joe then asked the crowd to pretend to call hogs, and then invited sound manager Joe Santarpia to do the same. Stu then picked up an Intrasport shirt from a fan and told them they weren't playing it at the show, but would next tour, followed be an Intrasport tease. Flight b741 contained a false start due to Amby playing in the wrong key. Ice V contained a Head On/Pill tease and a Down Under (Men At Work) tease on drums. Dirt through Let Me Mend The Past featured Joey on acoustic guitar. Dirt conained a “Taylor” (Jack Johnson) tease. Mirage City was introduced as Paradise City (Guns N' Roses) followed by a Welcome to the Jungle quote from Amby. During Let Me Mend The Past, Ambrose crowdsurfed on an inflatable boat. Following Le Risque, Joey shouted out Jackson Devereux and Allen Dobbins (the stream film crew). Gondii contained a Dragon quote. The Silver Cord contained Extinction quotes. Daily Blues was quoted before Venusian 1, which was stopped halfway through due to the barricade being broken. During the stop, Joey called his mom and Stu and Joey sung part of Vegemite acapella, which was "performed" for the first time since 2016-05-14. Gaia, which was incomplete, featured a drum solo with a Motor Spirit tease. The Great Chain of Being was incomplete. Gaia Outro was on the printed setlist after Motor Spirit, but was cut. Poster by Jason Galea Normal - 2500 Foil - 500

Slow Jam 1 contained Crumbling Castle and Am I In Heaven? teases. This Thing contained Am I In Heaven? teases and quotes. Am I In Heaven? contained The Land Before Timeland, Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) and Witchcraft teases and a Slow Jam 1 jam with lyrics, and featured improvised alternate lyrics. Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs. Nuclear Fusion featured community taper Mystery Jack for the vocal intro. Hog Calling Contest was teased prior to Antarctica, which contained Am I In Heaven? teases. Boogieman Sam contained La Grange (ZZ Top) teases and a Riff Raff (AC/DC) jam. Following Boogieman Sam, Joey mentioned that the band would be performing at the Hollywood Bowl with the L.A. Philharmonic on their upcoming tour in 2025, which was previously unannounced at the time. Texas Flood and Pride and Joy (Stevie Ray Vaughan) were teased prior to Daily Blues, which contained Hot Water teases. Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases, This Thing quotes, Forty Six and 2 (Tool) teases and Master of the Universe (Hawkwind) teases and quotes. Gamma Knife was unfinished. Ice V contained The Lord of Lightning teases. The Lord of Lightning contained Cellophane teases. Le Risque featured Jay Weinberg on drums. Additionally, Cavs got an audience member to perform a laugh for the song and brought Jay's wife Chloe on stage to perform the 'Let's Ride' vocal part. Following Le Risque, Amby quoted I Love L.A. (Randy Newman).

Mirage City was introduced as a "country song," featured Stu on acoustic guitar and contained a jam with lyrics of I’ll Be Gone (Spectrum) and a Riff Raff (AC/DC) tease. Raw Feel also featured Stu on acoustic guitar. Ice V contained Hog Calling Contest teases. Ambrose quoted the "one million dollars" line from Austin Powers and "Scotty Doesn't Know" from EuroTrip in the intro to Magma. The Dripping Tap was introduced as being sponsored by Pepto Bismol and contained You Can Be Your Silhouette and Machine Gun (Jimi Hendrix) teases. Work This Time was on the written setlist after Raw Feel but was not played.

Mr. Beat contained People-Vultures and Magma teases. Dirt and Mirage City featured Joey on acoustic guitar. Mirage City had an alternate slower outro section. Amby quoted Tomorrow (Silverchair) prior to The Dripping Tap, which contained Theia teases and quotes. Let Me Mend The Past contained an It Ain't Me, Babe (Bob Dylan) quote. Gaia featured a drum solo by Cavs.

Rattlesnake contained Nuclear Fusion, O.N.E. and Automation teases and Honey teases & quotes. Ice V contained Mirage City teases. Hog Calling Contest featured Joey on acoustic guitar. Following Set Amby quoted She'll Be Coming 'Round the Mountain (traditional).  Magenta Mountain contained The Grim Reaper quotes.

Antarctica was dedicated to "all the polar bears in denial" and contained Daily Blues quotes and Ice V and Block of Ice (Osees) teases. Ice V contained Head On/Pill and Blindness (The Fall) teases. Gamma Knife contained Converge teases.  People-Vultures contained Iron Lung teases & quotes and Phantom Island quotes. Stu said "Free Palestine" before Boogieman Sam, which contained an Eternal Return vocal jam, Am I In Heaven? teases and a Riff Raff (AC/DC) tease. Slow Jam 1 contained Am I In Heaven? teases. Am I In Heaven? was unfinished and contained a Sad Pilot jam and Riff Raff (AC/DC) teases. The intro to Self-Immolate contained Am I In Heaven? teases and a drum solo where Stu, Joey, and an audience member shaved most of Stu's head.

This show featured the debuts of Jailbreak (AC/DC) and the synth outro of Flamethrower. Ambrose sung along to the walkout music, which was Party All the Time (Eddie Murphy). Antarctica contained Hot Water and Forty Six and 2 (Tool) teases. Before Hypertension, the band talked about Stu's new guitar, mentioning Jimi Hendrix and Dimebag Darrell, and joking that they wanted to play Little Wing on the table, but Cavs said no because he wanted to play Foxy Lady and Cookie wanted to play She's So Fine. Boogieman Sam was teased before Ice V, which contained Blindness (The Fall) teases. Ambrose quoted “Good day, good evening, and good night!” from The Truman Show before Rats In The Sky. Jailbreak was impromptu/not on the written setlist, unfinished, and contained a Rats In the Sky outro. The Fourth Colour was on the printed setlist after Crumbling Castle but was not played.
data.soundcheck: Motor Spirit, Crumbling Castle > The Fourth Colour

data.jamchart_notes: A rendition including a metal section and whammy from Stu, as well as the origin story for the music video.
data.shownotes: This show featured the debut of Superposition. The Fourth Colour contained a Dripping Tap jam with lyrics. Band manager Michelle's son Laurence joined the band on stage for Straws in the Wind, which contained Phantom Island quotes and Ambrose chanting "free free Palestine". The audience continued the Palestine chants after the song, with the band repeating the slogan once along with them and then again during Minimum Brain Size. Before Nuclear Fusion, Joey thanked King Stingray and DJ Crenshaw. A fan named Tom provided the vocal intro on Nuclear Fusion wearing a Bullant shirt. The rock version of Theia was performed, which contained a Land Before Timeland jam and Iron Lung teases & quotes. Before Ice V, which was dedicated to "the incredible country called Greece", Joey told the story of his appearance in the Ice V music video, which was filmed on the island of Idra. The song itself contained Ain't It Funky Now (James Brown) teases. Digital Black was preceded by a tease of A New World. Float Along – Fill Your Lungs contained a Motor Spirit jam with lyrics, a Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg tease, Theia teases and quotes, and a Muddy Water and Superposition tease. Welcome to an Altered Future was on the printed setlist before Digital Black but was not played.

data.jamchart_notes: Featured Joey on Flute, an Aqualung (Jethro Tull) quote, and teases of Ants & Bats and Blindness (The Fall).
data.shownotes: Slow Jam 1 featured Ambrose on saxophone and contained an Am I In Heaven? tease. Empty was performed for the first time since 2014-12-19 (644 show gap), and was performed with flute for the first time. Hot Wax was played by request of Wayne Gordon (who recorded I'm In Your Mind Fuzz and Quarters! at Daptone Studios and made a brief appearance on stage) and contained an Am I In Heaven? tease. A fan named Callum was brought onto stage to play Superbug on Stu's guitar instead of Stu. Magenta Mountain contained Forty Six & 2 (Tool) and Magma teases. The Grim Reaper contained Forty Six & 2 (Tool) teases and Intergalactic, Sabotage (both Beastie Boys), and Torture Chamber quotes. Following The Grim Reaper, Joey said he was ripping off Wes Borland (of Limp Bizkit), and Ambrose said he needed a red hat (Fred Durst's signature hat). Swan Song contained Magenta Mountain teases and quotes. Le Risque featured Jay Weinberg on drums instead of Cavs. Ice V featured Joey on flute during the intro and contained a quote of Aqualung (Jethro Tull) and teases of Ants & Bats and Blindness (The Fall). Raw Feel contained Am I In Heaven? teases. Hot Water contained I'm In Your Mind and Robot Stop teases.  Following Hot Water, Joey shouted out festival act The Mystery Lights, saying they were the first band they co-headlined with in America. Boogieman Sam contained The Bitter Boogie, Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) and Riff Raff (AC/DC) teases. During Straws In The Wind, Ambrose walked through the crowd to Jason at the soundboard and when he returned to stage, he did an impression of Fred Durst. After Straws In The Wind, the band pretended it was Jason's birthday and sang Happy Birthday to him. During Pleura, Joey said "Fuck Donald Trump", with Ambrose responding "Juicy [Jason] for President!" Dimathaya Burarrwanga and Yimila Gurruwiwi from King Stingray joined the band for Rattlesnake on yiḏaki (didgeridoo), and Dimathaya quoted Treaty (Yothu Yindi). At the end of the show, Joey said Free Palestine and Ambrose led the crowd in a chant of "Free Free Palestine".

data.showtitle: Yadaki Psych Set at Field of Vision
data.shownotes: This show was performed on the Timeland Stage after King Gizzard's headlining set. The Ice V and Lookin' Out jams featured Joey, Ambrose, and Lucas. The first jam contained Treaty (Yothu Yindi) quotes and unknown lyrics. The second jam also contained unknown lyrics. The Ice V jam contained multiple sections of lyrical improv and freestyling from Dimathaya, unknown possibly improvised lyrics from Ambrose, including the "black market bargain spinal cords" lines found in the previous Europe tour, Gloria (T.H.E.M.), Shake Your Daughter (Revolver & Sun), Stoned Mullet, Killing in the Name (Rage Against The Machine), Torture Chamber, and Whole Lotta Love (Led Zeppelin) quotes. The Lookin' Out jam contained Hypertension teases and Treaty and Ghost Spirits (both Yothu Yindi) quotes.

This show featured the live debut of Fishing For Fishies. Ice V had Muddy Water, Blindness (The Fall) and Extinction teases, as well as Joey playing riffs from various Set jams on guitar. A cake decorated to look like the Flight b741 album cover was brought on stage during Dreams. The Grim Reaper had a lyric change to "the grim reaper shits on your chest" and had quotes from Torture Chamber, Sabotage (Beastie Boys), Bonkers (Dizzee Rascal) and Rollin' (Limp Bizkit). During the song Ambrose pushed his face into the cake. Cavs went crowd surfing during Fishing For Fishies. Ambrose introduced Smoke & Mirrors as a song about someone who "did us dirty" and thanked the audience for the cake. Ambrose went crowd surfing during the song. Magma, which didn't include the "rumble" section, contained a Smoke & Mirrors jam with lyrics.

Theia contained a Gilgamesh quote and The Silver Cord lyrics from Theia's extended mix. Shanghai contained a Grow Wings and Fly jam with lyrics. The Grim Reaper featured Ambrose performing the first two verses in the mosh pit, had a lyric changed to "the Grim Reaper cashes the Czech Republic" and contained Sabotage (Beastie Boys) (with lyrics changed to "listen all of Prague it's a sabotage"), Intergalatic (Beastie Boys), Bonkers (Dizzee Rascal), Torture Chamber, and Rollin' (Air Raid Vehicle) (Limp Bizkit) quotes. Ice V contained Superposition and Blindness (The Fall) teases. Candles contained a Superposition tease. Sense and Flamethrower (Outro) were swapped on the printed setlist.

data.jamchart_notes: An ambient jam minus Cavs (bathroom break) starts off this Ice V which includes the intro of Panpsych. Cavs returns before they launch into the longest non-electronic rendition of the song yet, with plenty of teases.
data.shownotes: This show was played with The Queensland Symphony Orchestra conducted by Chad Kelly. The Intermission Jam contained Panpsych teases. Ice V contained Blindness (The Fall), Ain't It Funky Now (James Brown), The Land Before Timeland, Head On/Pill and Am I In Heaven? teases.
